Using `$lookup` you would need to merge all documents from both collections into single document and then run some set logic on it to remove duplicates. 1[6 MB is the maximum size][1] of a single MongoDB document so you may reach this threshold easily if your collections are big. 

MongoDB 4.2 brings new [$merge][2] operator which will allow you to &quot;join&quot; two collections:

    db.colA.aggregate([
        {
            $merge: {
                into: &quot;colB&quot;,
                on: &quot;Id&quot;,
                whenMatched: &quot;replace&quot;
            }
        }
    ])


  [1]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/limits/#BSON-Document-Size
  [2]: https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge/

