There is 2 main problem in your code.

1. The font size is decleared in relative unite (em)
2. Div1, Div2 and Div3 are child and grand child of one another.

So the issue is, each div&#39;s font size is changing depending on it&#39;s parent div.

Possible solution.
1. If you need parent child relationship between divs then change font-size unite to px.

2. If there is no problem separating the divs from each other and add one after one as sibling. then you can use relative unite for font size.

**Note** : don&#39;t use transition property all for huge number of items which&#39;s transition are triggered at the same time. It creates performance issue.

Also try to avoid * selector if you are adding transition on a huge number of element.
 Define specific property which you want to change. It also improve performance.

## Option one - separating divs

&lt;script async src=&quot;//jsfiddle.net/vg1dtLrk/embed/html,css,result/&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: false babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    .large .animate {
      font-size: 3em;
    }

    .animate {
      transition: font-size 0.5s;
    }

    body {
      font-size: 1em;
      font-family: sans-serif;
    }

    button {
      margin-bottom: 25px;
    }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;button onclick=&quot;document.getElementById(&#39;text-container&#39;).classList.toggle(&#39;large&#39;)&quot;&gt;Toggle&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;div id=&quot;text-container&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;one&quot; class=&quot;animate&quot;&gt;
        One

      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;two&quot; class=&quot;animate&quot;&gt;
        Two
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;three&quot; class=&quot;animate&quot;&gt;
        Three
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div id=&quot;four&quot;&gt;
        Four
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

